  "doc_id": "49296",
  "text": "Multiple infections represent a potentially greater risk to human health. Single Anopheles mosquito carrying sporozoites of 3 Plasmodium species, P. knowlesi, P. falciparum, and P. vivax, was discovered in southern Vietnam [23] . The course of infection with P. knowlesi is dependent on the host. In its natural host, infection results in prolonged low-level parasitemia, whereas in the other hosts parasitemia rise rapidly, and the infection is responsible for severe complications and may be fatal [CITATION_1] . Yet so far, no evidence of man-to-man transmission of P. knowlesi has been found, and this species is considered enzootic [CITATION_2] .",
